# Microsoft Entra ID - Roles

## Entra ID Roles
| Role | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| Global Administrator | Full directory access, connect on-prem to Azure |
| User Administrator | Manage users and groups |
| Application Administrator | Manage apps and service principals |
| Other Roles | Helpdesk, Security Admin, etc. |

## Azure RBAC Roles
| Role | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| Owner | Full access to Azure resources |
| Contributor | Create & manage resources |
| Reader | View resources |

## Scope
- Management Group → Subscription → Resource Group → Resource

### Key Difference
- Entra ID roles = Identity management  
- Azure RBAC = Resource management

### Interview Line
"Entra roles manage directory objects, Azure RBAC manages Azure resource access."


# Microsoft Entra ID - Identity Protection (P2)

## Purpose
Detect and respond to risky users/sign-ins using ML & threat intelligence

## Risk Type
| Type | Meaning | Action |
|------|---------|--------|
| Sign-in Risk | Suspicious login attempt | MFA, Block |
| User Risk | Compromised account probability | Force password reset |

## Risk Detections
- Impossible travel
- Anonymous IP
- Atypical sign-ins

## Practical Flow
1. User signs in
2. Identity Protection evaluates risk
3. Risk signals passed to Conditional Access
4. Conditional Access enforces actions (MFA, password reset, block)

### Interview One-liner
"Identity Protection detects risky users/sign-ins and integrates with Conditional Access to automatically enforce security."
